# Opinion Writing + Evidence

Research consistently shows:

# Opinion Writing

depends on:

```text id="m7o2qe"
claim
and
support reasoning
```

Opinion writing is NOT:

```text id="r4o8qe"
personal feeling
only
```

Students learn:

```text id="x1o5qe"
state opinion
→ give reasons
→ support with evidence
→ organize ideas
→ conclude clearly
```

This develops:

* argument reasoning
* communication
* evidence use
* organization
* critical thinking

This becomes:

# Evidence-Based Opinion Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p8o1qe"
opinion
needs
no support
```

or:

```text id="u3o6qe"
strong opinion
=
loud opinion
```

Some may:

```text id="c5o9qe"
repeat
opinion
without
reasons
```

without understanding:

```text id="k2o4qe"
opinions
become
stronger
with
evidence
```

Example:

students may write:

```text id="n6o3qe"
Dogs are best.
Because I said so.
```

instead of:

```text id="t1o7qe"
Dogs are good pets
because
they are loyal,
active,
and helpful.
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="q7o2qe"
reasoned argument
```

For Grade 4:

focus includes:

Opinion Writing:

* clear claim
* reasons
* evidence
* transitions
* conclusion

Evidence:

* examples
* facts
* experiences
* text support
* explanations

Important structure:

```text id="a5o3qe"
opinion
+
reasons
+
evidence
=
strong writing
```

